Movement For The Development Of Itsekiri Oil and Gas Producing Communities has petitioned President
Muhammadu Buhari over the margnalisation of Itsekiri nation in project execution and employment opportunities
by international oil and gas companies (IOCs) in the region. In a petition signed by its chairman, Isaac Botosan, secretary, Irone Maurice and publicity secretary, Stephen Atete, the group gave the President a 14-day ultimatum to address the injustice. Failure to do so, the group said it would shut down operations of IOCs in the area. The group alleged that despite the fact that Itsekiri nation contributes over 28 percent to Nigeria’s crude oil and gas resources, there is zero federal presence in the land. It also said that while their graduates are jobless, IOCs employ no indigenes to work in their fields. “We, the Itsekiri people continue to agonize the apparent aberration of the Local Content Act as it affects direct employment opportunities into Chevron Nigeria Limited, Shell Petroleum Development Company, SPDC and other
IOCs, operating in our communities. These companies surreptitiously employ non indigenes and fly them to work in
Escravos and other Itsekiri Offshore Locations, while our eminently qualified graduates as well as technicians roam the streets and continue to live at the mercy of their indigent and aging parents”.